1
00:00:55,780 --> 00:00:58,120
我一直想跟你谈谈
I've been meaning to talk with you.

2
00:00:58,730 --> 00:01:00,880
真可怕  不是吗
It's terrifying, isn't it?

3
00:01:02,290 --> 00:01:05,210
总统和我有一个简单的请求
The president and I have a simple request.

4
00:01:06,390 --> 00:01:08,090
告诉我们你看到了什么
Tell us what you see.

5
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,250
如果你周围有任何东西
If anything in your environment

6
00:01:11,250 --> 00:01:13,380
让你觉得奇怪  不对劲
strikes you as a bit odd, a bit off,

7
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:15,040
拿起电话
pick up the phone.

8
00:01:15,230 --> 00:01:18,980
不管是个包裹  还是不太对劲的人
Whether it's a package or a person that seems out of place,

9
00:01:18,980 --> 00:01:20,900
我们希望你通知我们
we'd love you to let us know.

10
00:01:21,770 --> 00:01:24,600
因为如今外面有很多杂音
Because there's a lot of noise out there these days.

11
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:27,860
媒体叽叽喳喳  沉湎于过去
A noisy press that's choosing to dwell on the past

12
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:30,070
却不关注当下的事
instead of what's happening right now.

13
00:01:30,910 --> 00:01:33,310
我丈夫和我想保护你
My husband and I want to protect you.

14
00:01:33,980 --> 00:01:36,750
两周后  你们将前往投票箱
In two weeks' time, you will be heading to the ballot box

15
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:40,340
决定你们要生活在怎样的国家里
to decide what kind of country you want to live in.

16
00:01:41,090 --> 00:01:42,910
这个选择影响深远
It's a profound choice.

17
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:46,020
但不管谁赢得选举
But no matter who wins this election,

18
00:01:46,020 --> 00:01:48,070
我们得通力合作
we're going to need to work together,

19
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:50,110
互相照应
watch out for each other,

20
00:01:50,230 --> 00:01:52,720
是的  也互相监督
and, yes, watch each other,

21
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:55,110
以确保所有人的安全
to keep us all safe and sound.

22
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,280
告诉我们你看到了什么
Tell us what you see.

23
00:01:58,430 --> 00:02:01,640
我叫克莱尔·安德伍德  我认可这则信息
My name is Claire Underwood, and I approve this message.

24
00:02:04,150 --> 00:02:05,490
我们要再拍一条吗
Should we do one more?

25
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:24,780
民主党来了吗
Did the Democrats show?

26
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:27,410
他们没让人失望  几乎都来了  先生
They didn't disappoint. Almost every member, sir.

27
00:02:27,410 --> 00:02:29,810
-几乎  -我列了到场名单
- Almost. - I have a list of those who did.

28
00:02:29,810 --> 00:02:32,990
各位国会议员  我不需要《华盛顿先驱报》
My fellow congressmen, I do not need the Washington Herald

29
00:02:32,990 --> 00:02:36,690
告诉我白宫里住了个恶棍
to tell me that a scoundrel lives in the White House.

30
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:38,840
我看到民主党来了
I can see the Democrats are here.

31
00:02:38,850 --> 00:02:41,010
他们急着辩论
They're eager to debate.

32
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,750
我对过道另一边的先生们说
I say to the gentlemen on the other side of the aisle...

33
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:44,880
谢谢
thank you.

34
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:47,580
我们是否该调查总统
Should we investigate the president

35
00:02:47,580 --> 00:02:50,290
在就任副总统期间犯下的罪行
for crimes committed while he was vice president?

36
00:02:50,290 --> 00:02:53,140
我说  好  我们辩论吧
I say, yes. Let's debate.

37
00:02:53,140 --> 00:02:57,910
我们整日整夜地辩论这恶棍
Let's debate this miscreant all day and all night.

38
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:01,840
议长女士  议事询问
Madam Speaker. Parliamentary inquiry.

39
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,690
佐治亚州的议员
The gentleman from Georgia

40
00:03:02,690 --> 00:03:04,620
请提出他的议事询问
may state the nature of his parliamentary inquiry.

41
00:03:04,620 --> 00:03:06,510
难道按众议院规则
Do the rules of the House not require

42
00:03:06,510 --> 00:03:08,730
总统不是该受到正式邀请才能出席吗
the president be formally invited in order to attend?

43
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,140
议长女士  容我说一句
Madam Speaker, if I may...

44
00:03:10,140 --> 00:03:12,310
议长有请南卡罗莱纳州议员说话
The Speaker recognizes the gentleman from South Carolina.

45
00:03:12,310 --> 00:03:15,440
总统今天戴了他的国会胸针
The president is wearing his congressional pin today

46
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:18,600
所以他可以出席一切会议
and is thereby welcome to any and all proceedings.

47
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:21,530
议长女士  议长女士
Madam Speaker! Madam Speaker!

48
00:03:22,260 --> 00:03:23,300
按众议院规则
Rules of the House state

49
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:25,280
前众议院成员若与议题
that former members are not allowed on the floor

50
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,880
有直接关系则不得参与辩论
when they have interest in the matter under debate.

51
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:29,260
议长女士
Madam Speaker,

52
00:03:29,270 --> 00:03:30,910
总统对今天的议题
the president has no interest

53
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:33,980
既无关联  也无意见
or opinion on the matter being debated today.

54
00:03:34,970 --> 00:03:37,350
众议院安静  众议院安静
The House suspend. The House will suspend.

55
00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:40,110
议长女士  我还在讲话
Madam Speaker, I still do have the floor,

56
00:03:40,110 --> 00:03:42,110
而且我难以相信
and I find it hard to believe

57
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:45,660
总统对议题无话可说
the president wouldn't have an opinion on the matter being discussed.

58
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:47,430
如果佛罗里达州议员
If the good gentleman from Florida

59
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:49,680
肯让出点时间
would yield a portion of his time,

60
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:53,130
他的疑问肯定能得到解答
I assure him it will satisfy his query.

61
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:59,300
我给党领袖三分钟时间
I yield three minutes to the leader.

62
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:03,230
我把我的时间让给前南卡罗莱纳州议员
And I yield my time to the former congressman from South Carolina

63
00:04:03,230 --> 00:04:05,940
现美国总统
and the President of the United States.

64
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:11,330
议事程序  议事询问
Point of order! Parliamentary inquiry!

65
00:04:11,790 --> 00:04:13,720
议事询问
Parliamentary inquiry!

66
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:16,690
议事询问
Parliamentary inquiry!

67
00:04:16,770 --> 00:04:19,210
总统先生  这太不寻常了
Mr. President. This is beyond the norm.

68
00:04:19,210 --> 00:04:20,480
我不在乎
I don't care.

69
00:04:22,050 --> 00:04:23,980
我不在乎
I don't care.

70
00:04:24,910 --> 00:04:27,530
而且我也不在乎
And I also do not care

71
00:04:27,530 --> 00:04:30,060
你们的调查委员会
about your investigative committees.

72
00:04:30,060 --> 00:04:34,440
不  那不是我今天关心的东西
No, that is not what I care about today.

73
00:04:36,690 --> 00:04:38,330
众议院安静
The House will cease.

74
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:44,190
那不是我今天关心的东西
That is not what I care about today.

75
00:04:45,670 --> 00:04:47,590
我要去出席
I am on my way

76
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:51,960
一个美国爱国者的葬礼
to the funeral of an American patriot.

77
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:55,890
一个好人  一个丈夫
A good man, a husband...

78
00:04:56,940 --> 00:04:58,010
一个父亲
a father...

79
00:04:58,390 --> 00:05:01,990
在美国境内被人砍头
who was beheaded on American soil.

80
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:04,760
众议院
And this chamber

81
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:08,390
却在今天辩论我
chooses to debate me?

82
00:05:08,810 --> 00:05:11,330
-众议院安静  -我要求
- The House will suspend. - I asked to speak

83
00:05:11,340 --> 00:05:15,730
向众议院发表讲话  却遭到拒绝
to a full session of this chamber and my requests were denied.

84
00:05:15,730 --> 00:05:18,090
-议长女士  -总统先生  你必须让出说话权
- Madam Speaker! - Mr. President, you must yield the floor.

85
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:20,930
我不会退让的  议长女士
I will not yield, Madam Speaker.

86
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:24,190
因为我等不了
Because I cannot wait.

87
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:31,410
其中一个杀人犯
One of the murderers...

88
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:37,830
杀害了吉姆·米勒先生的一个杀人犯
One of the murderers who killed Mr. Jim Miller...

89
00:05:38,450 --> 00:05:39,930
还逍遥法外
is still out there.

90
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:41,860
正在逃逸
At large.

91
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:47,880
你们还要多少证据
How much more proof do you people need?

92
00:05:50,310 --> 00:05:55,030
我要求所有众议院议员表明立场
I demand that every member of this House take a stand.

93
00:05:55,030 --> 00:05:58,760
就像曾经的罗斯福  再之前的威尔逊
Like FDR before, and Wilson before him.

94
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:00,990
我要求国会
I demand that this Congress

95
00:06:00,990 --> 00:06:04,700
正式对哈里发国宣战
declare a formal declaration of war against ICO,

96
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:06,930
在本土  也在海外
both here and abroad.

97
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:07,980
动议休会
Motion to adjourn.

98
00:06:07,980 --> 00:06:09,850
-支持  -众议院休会
- Second! - The House will adjourn.

99
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:12,720
-总统请停止讲话  -我不会停止
- The president will cease. - I will not cease!

100
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:15,360
我绝不停止
I will never cease.

101
00:06:15,410 --> 00:06:19,330
我要求国会宣布美利坚合众国
I demand that this Congress declare a state of war

102
00:06:19,330 --> 00:06:21,640
已经并且正在
has existed and does exist

103
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:25,120
与哈里发国交战
between ICO and the United States of America.

104
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:29,430
我要求所有众议院成员留在这里
And I demand that every member of this House stay in this chamber

105
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,490
不管要多久
for as long as it takes,

106
00:06:31,490 --> 00:06:34,480
直到你们对我的要求作出表决
until you bring my request to a vote.

107
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:37,640
否则你们将被历史
Or you will all go down in history

108
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,880
铭记为懦夫
as cowards!

109
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,360
懦夫
Cowards!

110
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,480
请警卫官带走总统
The sergeant at arms will remove the president.

111
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:47,070
议长女士  我重复  我要求投票
Madam Speaker, I repeat. I demand a vote.

112
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,240
我不会退让
I will not yield.

113
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:52,140
我不会退让
I will not yield.

114
00:06:52,210 --> 00:06:55,260
我不会退让
I will not yield.

115
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:59,840
