- You're angry. - I am.

354
00:22:09,650 --> 00:22:11,420
我被提了问  我回答了
I was asked a question and I answered.

355
00:22:11,420 --> 00:22:13,410
说得太轻了
That's the least of it.

356
00:22:14,610 --> 00:22:17,150
好吧  我现在不想谈这个
Okay, well, I don't want to talk about it right now.

357
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:20,180
你是想输掉竞选吗  是吗
Are you trying to lose this election? Are you?

358
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:21,620
威尔  得了
Will, stop it.

359
00:22:21,620 --> 00:22:23,760
你维护的这女人
This woman that you're defending...

360
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:26,340
她儿子砍了别人的头
Her son just cut someone's head off.

361
00:22:26,490 --> 00:22:27,740
他还逍遥在外
And he's still out there somewhere.

362
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:29,770
-你知道这看上去什么样吗  -别说了
- Do you understand what this looks like? - Stop it.

363
00:22:30,710 --> 00:22:33,240
你知道我们儿子为什么睡不着吗
Do you want to know why our son can't sleep?

364
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:35,880
他才八岁  却失眠了
He's eight years old, and he can't sleep.

365
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:37,880
因为他做恶梦
Because he's having nightmares.

366
00:22:38,730 --> 00:22:40,090
因为他觉得
Because he thinks

367
00:22:40,090 --> 00:22:42,540
酒店里有头黑色大狗在到处跑
there's a big black dog running around the hotel.

368
00:22:42,540 --> 00:22:43,850
-狗  -对
- Dog? - Yes.

369
00:22:43,850 --> 00:22:46,920
他闭上眼睛  就能听到它咆哮
He closes his eyes, and he can hear it growling.

370
00:22:47,190 --> 00:22:48,830
他害怕  威尔
He's scared, Will.

371
00:22:53,940 --> 00:22:58,450
我说那些话是因为那女人也是受害者
I said what I said because that woman is a victim.

372
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:00,950
我们都是
We all are.

373
00:23:01,910 --> 00:23:03,400
这必须停止了
And it has to stop.

374
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,490
我希望你赢
I want you to win.

375
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,480
去给自己倒一杯酒  我就回来
Get yourself a drink. I'll be right back.

376
00:23:30,930 --> 00:23:34,960
那是他母亲  这是汉娜的回应
That's the mother. And this is Hannah's response.

377
00:23:35,850 --> 00:23:37,060
她不是罪犯
She's not a criminal

378
00:23:37,060 --> 00:23:39,610
不该因为她儿子的罪受惩罚
and should not be punished for the sins of her son.

379
00:23:39,610 --> 00:23:41,670
我知道我们都反对
We all, I know, reject

380
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:45,790
这两位困惑受伤的青年的说法和行为
the rhetoric and actions of these damaged, troubled young men.

381
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:49,220
我是说  这是该反省的时候
What I mean is, this is a time for reflection,

382
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:49,820
而不是进攻
not aggression...

383
00:23:49,820 --> 00:23:53,090
她没有表示宽恕  但表示了同情
So she's not condoning it, but it is sympathetic.

384
00:23:53,090 --> 00:23:55,180
把约书亚和扎克瑞说成
Plays into the idea that Joshua and Zachary

385
00:23:55,180 --> 00:23:57,160
一对儿寻找目标的困惑青年
were just a pair of troubled kids looking for a cause,

386
00:23:57,160 --> 00:23:59,760
跟普通学校枪击手没什么区别
no different than some school shooter.

387
00:24:00,450 --> 00:24:03,090
视频转发超过10万次了
The post has been shared over 100,000 times.

388
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:06,470
我想跟她谈谈
I want to talk with her.

389
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:09,330
-汉娜  -那个母亲
- Hannah? - The mother.

390
00:24:10,340 --> 00:24:12,640
我们一直对你在哪露面十分小心
We've been very careful about where you appear.

391
00:24:13,350 --> 00:24:16,560
-莉安  能让我们单独待会儿吗  -当然
- LeAnn, will you excuse us for a moment? - Of course.

392
00:24:24,090 --> 00:24:26,010
我们得加大恐惧感
We need to dial up the terror.

393
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:28,420
那个母亲能帮我们做到
And the mother can help us with that.

394
00:24:28,420 --> 00:24:31,570
但那样我们还得找到马斯特森
But that also means we have to locate Masterson.

395
00:24:31,780 --> 00:24:32,780
尽快
Soon.

396
00:24:38,070 --> 00:24:39,730
汤姆在等我
Tom is waiting for me.

397
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:41,470
你去吧
Well, you go on.

398
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:50,790
弗兰西斯
Francis...

399
00:24:52,690 --> 00:24:55,310
我不该在葬礼上哭
I shouldn't have cried at the funeral.

400
00:24:57,080 --> 00:25:00,050
-不  那效果很好  -对我不好
- No, it played beautifully. - Not for me.

401
00:25:04,310 --> 00:25:05,300
跟我来
Come with me.

402
00:25:07,340 --> 00:25:08,710
来吧  告诉他你要迟点到
Come on. Just tell him you'll be late.

403
00:25:16,670 --> 00:25:18,570
-总统先生  -没事  警官
- Mr. President. - It's all right, Officer.

404
00:25:18,570 --> 00:25:19,450
夫人
Ma'am.

405
00:25:21,870 --> 00:25:23,300
能给我你的目镜吗
May I have your scope?

406
00:25:23,870 --> 00:25:26,930
你枪上的目镜  我保证还回来
Scope on your gun. I promise I'll give it back.

407
00:25:32,450 --> 00:25:34,360
谢谢  过来
Thank you. Come here.

408
00:25:46,130 --> 00:25:49,580
如果你把目镜举在离脸稍远处
Now, if you just hold the scope a little a ways from your face...

409
00:25:50,190 --> 00:25:52,700
往下看  直向下  草坪对面
and look down, straight down, across the lawn...

410
00:25:53,670 --> 00:25:54,990
门那里
right to the gate.

411
00:26:00,060 --> 00:26:01,100
看到他们了吗
You see them?

412
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:08,260
那些人想要发声  有些是支持的  有些反对
Those people want a voice. Some for, some against.

413
00:26:08,860 --> 00:26:10,620
他们也在草坪那头往这边看
And they're looking back across the lawn,

414
00:26:10,620 --> 00:26:13,090
看这栋房子  这些窗户
toward this house and these windows...

415
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:15,000
他们在想
and they're thinking,

416
00:26:15,780 --> 00:26:17,320
"不知道总统
"I wonder what the president

417
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:19,630
和第一夫人今晚在做什么
and the First Lady are doing tonight.

418
00:26:20,390 --> 00:26:23,180
他们能保护我们吗"
And will they be able to protect us?"

419
00:26:26,090 --> 00:26:27,500
我该在场的
I should have been there.

420
00:26:28,590 --> 00:26:29,440
哪里
Where?

421
00:26:30,340 --> 00:26:33,490
你受枪伤时  我真该在场的
When you got shot. I wish I was there.

422
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,190
或许我还能
Maybe I could've...

423
00:26:36,570 --> 00:26:37,820
保护你
protected you.

424
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,980
你瞧  那些人只想
You see, all those people want...

425
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:49,770
有人保护他们  不用面对可怕的真相
is someone to keep them from what they're afraid to know.

426
00:26:54,790 --> 00:26:58,780
总统和第一夫人今晚要做什么呢  弗兰西斯
And what are the president and First Lady doing tonight, Francis?

427
00:26:59,140 --> 00:27:01,610
托马斯不是还等着你呢吗
Well, I believe Thomas is waiting for you.

428
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,400
谢谢  先生
Thank you, sir.

429
00:27:08,990 --> 00:27:10,340
我们明早见
I'll see you in the morning.

430
00:27:14,050 --> 00:27:15,470
你有烟吗
Do you have a smoke?

431
00:27:21,470 --> 00:27:22,590
谢谢
Thank you.

432
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:32,110
*我知道我的人民今晚在想什么*
*I know what my people are thinking tonight*

433
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:32,480
{\an9}BGM: I Wonder What the King Is Doing Tonight

434
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:37,570
*穿过阴影  他们漫步回家*
*As home through the shadows they wander*

435
00:27:39,590 --> 00:27:42,170
*大家都窃笑着*
*Everyone smiling in secret delight*

436
00:27:42,810 --> 00:27:45,800
*他们看着城堡  思索着*
*As they stare at the castle and ponder*

437
00:27:47,010 --> 00:27:49,900
*当风往这边吹*
*And whenever the wind blows this way*

438
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:53,450
*你几乎能听到大家说*
*You can almost hear everyone say*

439
00:27:54,530 --> 00:27:58,000
*不知国王今晚在做什么*
*I wonder what the king is doing tonight*

440
00:28:06,530 --> 00:28:08,270
我一直在找你
I've been looking for you.

441
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:10,580
我饿了
I got hungry.

442
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:13,180
所以去了主厨房
So I went down to the main kitchen.

443
00:28:13,830 --> 00:28:15,990
下面的人真不错
That's a lovely group of people you have down there.

444
00:28:15,990 --> 00:28:18,830
如果你需要什么  可以叫人拿上来
If there's anything you need, it can be brought up.

445
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:22,080
我直到吃在嘴里才知道自己需要什么
I didn't know what I needed until I was eating it.

446
00:28:23,210 --> 00:28:24,910
我听到了总统的声明
I heard the president's declaration.

447
00:28:26,420 --> 00:28:27,590
很有力
Very compelling.

448
00:28:32,950 --> 00:28:34,470
你究竟怎么想的
What did you really think?

449
00:28:34,930 --> 00:28:36,850
简直像真的一样
It was almost like the real thing.

450
00:28:55,970 --> 00:28:58,770
国安局的人很厉害  非常厉害
The NSA has good people. Very good.

451
00:28:58,770 --> 00:29:00,680
-太厉害了  -不如你厉害
- Too good. - Not as good as you.

452
00:29:01,110 --> 00:29:02,900
足以找到我的算法了
Good enough to find my algorithms.

453
00:29:02,900 --> 00:29:05,090
那不代表他们知道我们用它做了什么
That doesn't mean they knew what we were using them for.

454
00:29:05,090 --> 00:29:06,250
不不
No, no.

455
00:29:06,740 --> 00:29:09,120
前一秒  他们还叫我回家  然后紧接着
One second, they send me home, and then the next,

456
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,880
他们说  "回来"
they tell me, "Come back!"

457
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:13,330
他们肯定要监视我了  这是个陷阱
They'll been watching me. This is a trap.

458
00:29:13,330 --> 00:29:15,170
或是唯一的出路
Or the only way out.

459
00:29:15,170 --> 00:29:16,320
该死
God damn it.

460
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:18,040
-你想要出路吗  -你不想吗
- You want out? - Don't you?

461
00:29:22,030 --> 00:29:23,050
莉安
LeAnn...

462
00:29:25,580 --> 00:29:27,900
我们做了违法的事
we have done some illegal things here.

463
00:29:29,160 --> 00:29:30,680
还有其他竞选
There are other campaigns.

464
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:33,700
-如果你可以打入国安局  -那不可能
- If you can get into the NSA... - That's not possible.

465
00:29:33,700 --> 00:29:35,660
进入他们的系统  你可以解决的
...into their system, you can fix this.

466
00:29:35,660 --> 00:29:38,010
-你没听我说  -我听了
- You're not listening to me. - I am.

467
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:41,060
我了解安德伍德夫妇
I know the Underwoods.

468
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:45,080
我们如果想平安度过
The only way that we are gonna survive this...

469
00:29:45,410 --> 00:29:47,010
就得让他们赢
is if they win.

470
00:29:48,660 --> 00:29:50,280
你可以帮他们赢
You can help them win.

471
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:52,540
我知道你能
I know you can.

472
00:30:05,910 --> 00:30:08,170
你走后我就加入了报社
I got on the paper right around the time you left.

473
00:30:08,790 --> 00:30:10,510
你从时尚版块起步的吗
Did you start in Style?

474
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,830
都市
Metro desk.

475
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:14,240
然后我发了篇报道  一个街头时尚
But then I did this piece, a street fashion,

476
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:15,640
街头的孩子的报道
kids on the street thing.

477
00:30:17,070 --> 00:30:18,550
没想到你会叫我来
I'm surprised you asked for me.

478
00:30:19,650 --> 00:30:22,500
队伍里有些人员变化
Some people are being moved around and off the team.

479
00:30:23,330 --> 00:30:28,240
马斯特森的报道  "战争  有什么好处"
The Masterson story. "War, what is it good for?"

480
00:30:32,070 --> 00:30:34,970
你对调查性新闻感兴趣吗
Were you ever interested in investigative journalism?

481
00:30:35,230 --> 00:30:38,130
要问我  不是这种的就不叫新闻
If you ask me, if it's not investigating, it's not journalism.

482
00:30:41,810 --> 00:30:45,240
听这里的人说  你能让任何人对你开口
Word around here is you can get anybody to talk to you.

483
00:30:47,490 --> 00:30:50,270
过了8点  又有酒的话
After 8:00, with a drink in their hands...

484
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:52,090
是啊
yeah.

485
00:31:01,470 --> 00:31:03,510
他们说她是个...
She's the one they say you called a...

486
00:31:06,180 --> 00:31:07,060
你懂的
you know.

487
00:31:10,630 --> 00:31:11,830
对不起  我有点紧张
I'm sorry. I'm a little nervous.

488
00:31:11,830 --> 00:31:13,600
你算是传奇人物
You're sort of a legend and...

489
00:31:14,660 --> 00:31:16,500
报道总统的文章
articles on the president?

490
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:20,400
能跟你合作是莫大的荣幸
It'd be an honor to work with you in any capacity.

491
00:31:21,730 --> 00:31:22,970
能参与进来
To be part of this.

492
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:30,230
你们找到他了吗
Did you find him? Did you?

493
00:31:30,230 --> 00:31:31,890
再等一下就好
It'll only be another moment.

494
00:31:32,430 --> 00:31:34,420
因为我已经做尽了一切
Because I've done all I can.

495
00:31:34,680 --> 00:31:37,610
你们叫我做的一切  你知道的
Everything you told me to. You know that.

496
00:31:38,270 --> 00:31:39,860
他们知道的  是吧
They know that, don't they?

497
00:31:44,100 --> 00:31:45,120
安德伍德夫人
Mrs. Underwood.

498
00:31:46,300 --> 00:31:49,900
我想跟马斯特森女士说话
I was hoping to speak to Ms. Masterson.

499
00:31:51,500 --> 00:31:52,840
就我们俩
Just the two of us.

500
00:32:14,940 --> 00:32:16,260
有什么问题吗
Is there a problem?

501
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:18,980
这有点极端
It is a bit extreme.

502
00:32:20,020 --> 00:32:23,040
把禁飞令扩大到这样的范围
Expanding the no-fly list to this extent.

503
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:26,000
单是对签证的限制就前所未有
The restrictions on visas alone is unprecedented.

504
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:27,190
我们要如何解释
How do we justify?

505
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:28,740
白宫顾问已经讨论过了
The White House counsel's been all through that.

506
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:30,260
都白纸黑字写着了
It's there in black and white.

507
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:32,700
我们基本上是在
We're virtually closing down our borders

508
00:32:32,710 --> 00:32:35,910
-没有证据的情况下关闭国境  -会有的
- without any hard evidence to back it up. - It's coming.

509
00:32:35,910 --> 00:32:38,990
很多无辜的人正想进入这个国家
A lot of innocent people are trying to get into this country.

510
00:32:38,990 --> 00:32:40,920
他们可能因此受伤害
They could be hurt by this.

511
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:47,460
如此大的政策变动  我想好好做
A change in policy this big, I want it done right.

512
00:32:48,830 --> 00:32:51,030
我要你让世界知道
I want you to let the world know

513
00:32:51,030 --> 00:32:53,280
如果他们还想继续进入这个国家
that if they want to continue coming to this country

514
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:54,920
上我们的医院  我们的学校  
for our hospitals, our colleges,

515
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:58,110
我们的高尔夫球场什么的
our golf courses and God knows what else...

516
00:32:58,450 --> 00:32:59,610
他们光是
they're going to have to deliver

517
00:32:59,610 --> 00:33:03,110
把我的脑袋贴在棍子上烧是不够的
more than my head on the end of a burning stick.

518
00:33:04,700 --> 00:33:05,240
听着  凯茜
Now look, Cathy,

519
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:08,200
我知道你有辛苦经营的人脉
I know you have well-earned relationships out there.

520
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:09,320
都是老交情
Long-standing.

521
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:12,000
我没有保留  弗兰西斯  我都联络了
I'm not holding back, Francis. I have reached out.

522
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,620
那我需要你再加把劲  
Then I need you to reach further.

523
00:33:13,620 --> 00:33:15,130
我要可行的情报
I want actionable intelligence.

524
00:33:15,130 --> 00:33:17,540
我要知道哈里发国在哪  或者至少
I want to know where ICO is, or at the very least,

525
00:33:17,540 --> 00:33:19,330
所有人都在找他们
that everyone's out there looking.

526
00:33:19,850 --> 00:33:21,050
明白了吗
Are we clear?

527
00:33:21,530 --> 00:33:22,350
明白了
We're clear.

528
00:33:22,350 --> 00:33:24,410
谢谢  凯茜  我知道你不会让我失望
Thank you, Cathy. I know you won't let me down.

529
00:33:34,770 --> 00:33:35,770
他死了
He's dead.

530
00:33:36,820 --> 00:33:37,910
你是来告诉我这个的吗  
Is that why you're here?

531
00:33:37,910 --> 00:33:39,110
我们还在找他
We're still looking for him--

532
00:33:39,110 --> 00:33:42,550
因为如果他死了  我要见到他  摸到他
Because if he's dead, I want to see him. To touch him.

533
00:33:45,470 --> 00:33:46,800
-我是想帮忙  -马斯特森太太
- I'm trying to help... - Ms. Masterson,

534
00:33:46,800 --> 00:33:48,450
-但他没有联系我  -求你
- ...but he hasn't contacted me. - please.

535
00:33:48,450 --> 00:33:49,380
我也希望他联系我
I wish he would.

